a) Write a Java program to create an interface Area with one method AreaCompute() with

2 float parameters. Design 2 classes Rectangle and triangle implementing the Area

Interface. Input should be taken from the user using Buffered Reader class.

CODE:

package practical5;

import java.io.BufferedReader;

import java.io.InputStreamReader;

import java.io.IOException;

public class Practical5 {

public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {

float length, breadth;

System.out.println("Enter the length and breadth of Rectangle and Triangle : ");

BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader (new InputStreamReader(System.in));

length=Float.parseFloat(br.readLine());

breadth=Float.parseFloat(br.readLine());

Rectangle r = new Rectangle();

r.AreaCompute(length,breadth);

Triangle t = new Triangle();

t.AreaCompute (length, breadth);

}

}

rectangle

package practical5;

public class Rectangle implements Area {

@Override

public void AreaCompute(float a, float b) {

System.out.println("Area of Rectangle = "+(a+b));

} 
} 
Area 
package practical5; 
public interface Area 
{ 
public void AreaCompute(float a,float b); 
} 
Traingle 
package practical5; 
public class Triangle implements Area 
{ 
@Override public void AreaCompute(float a, float b) 
{ 
System.out.println("Area of Triangle = "+(a*b)/2); 
} 
}


b) Define 2 packages (i) Prime (ii) Factorial. Write a Java program to create a class

PrimeFact to import these packages.

CODE:
package Factorial; 
public class fact 
{ 
public void getfactorial(int n)
{ 
int fact=1; 
for(int i=1;i<=n;i++)
{ 
fact=fact*i; 
} 
System.out.println("Factorial of "+n+" is: "+fact); 
} 
} 
prime package Prime; 
public class primeno 
{ 
public void checkPrime(int n)
{ 
int count = 0; 
for(int i=2; i<n; i++) 
{ 
if(n%i == 0) 
{ 
count++; 
break; 
} 
} 
if(count==0) System.out.println(n+" It is a Prime Number."); 
else 
System.out.println(n+" It is not a Prime Number."); 
} 
} 
primeFact import Prime.*; 
import Factorial.*; 
public class PrimeFact 
{ 
public static void main(String[] args) 
{ 
primeno pr=new primeno(); 
fact f=new fact(); 
pr.checkPrime(3); 
f.getfactorial(5); 
} 
}
